-- CTC Media’s CTC TV Falls to Seventh Place, TNS-Global Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-07-26T17:01:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-26/ctc-media-s-ctc-tv-falls-to-seventh-place-tns-global-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s CTC television
channel fell to the seventh most-watched among Russian viewers
18 years and older in the week to July 22, from sixth a week
before, as its audience contracted, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, fell to 5.3 percent in the
week to July 22 from 5.4 percent a week earlier, while rival
Fifth Channel’s share rose to 5.6 percent from 5.1 percent in
the previous week, pushing it ahead of CTC to the sixth most-
watched in the country, data researcher TNS-Global said by e-
mail today.  CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old and
over fell to 5.8 percent from 5.9 percent, the data show. CTC
remained in fifth place among viewers 4 years old and over, TNS-
Global said.  Russia’s NTV Television was the most watched among both
categories. Government-controlled Rossiya-1 was the second-most
watched in both segments, pushing Pervyi Kanal to the third most
watched in both categories and TNT TV was fourth, the data show.
REN TV remained fifth-biggest in the audience of viewers 18
years and older in the week to July 22, the data showed.  To contact the reporters on this story:
